Methodology 3


Data Preparation

The data cleaning process involved handling missing values, standardizing formats, removing duplicates, correcting inconsistencies. This preparation ensured that the data was structured, enriched, and optimized for predictive modeling and visualization.


Model Selection

A predictive model using regression analysis was applied to estimate patient recovery outcomes based on various treatment factors. This approach is effective in identifying relationships between independent variables like treatment cost, length of stay, and recovery probability with the dependent variables, such as recovery rate and patient satisfaction. The regression model is particularly adept at handling continuous variables and can efficiently quantify the impact of different treatment plans on patient outcomes. By utilizing this model, healthcare providers can optimize treatment strategies, improve resource allocation, and offer more accurate predictions for patient recovery, ultimately enhancing the quality of care and reducing operational costs.


Model Development

The XGBClassifier model was trained and optimized using Healthcare data. The dataset was split into training and testing sets. The training set enabled the model to identify patterns, while the testing set assessed its ability to generalize to unseen data. This approach helps prevent overfitting, ensuring the model doesnt perform well only on the training data but also on new, unseen data. By using a test set, the models predictions remain unbiased and reliable.
